{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "More so, there is likely no inherent connection between objectively identifiable features of the influence, such as the kind of words used in a text output and its manipulativeness.",
    "Manipulative influence does not, as it were, 'wear its manipulativeness on the sleeve.'",
    "For example, the sentence 'you promised to give it to me!'",
    "may be part of a manipulative guilt trip or part of a perfectly benign and non-manipulative conversation.",
    "It seems unlikely that we can reliably classify the influence without considering the motivation or genesis of the influence, such as the intention of the manipulator."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}